item.title: TensorFlow on MacOS
item.description: I was very excited to start running TensorFlow Python programs on my Mac. I installed it using PIP, using the instructions provided by TensorFlow.org. On running my first TensorFlow program, the first thing it output was: 2018-11-25 19:13:07.524017: I tensorflow/core/platform/cpu_feature_guard.cc:141] Your CPU supports instructions that this TensorFlow binary was not compiled to use: SSE4.1 SSE4.2 AVX AVX2 FMA This didn’t look good, it turned out it’s just a warning. My program worked, but wasn’t running as fast as it could.
